Common Misconceptions
❌ Encryption is the same as Hashing.

Correct:

Encryption is reversible.

Hashing is not.

❌ Secret algorithms provide security.

Correct:

Modern cryptography assumes the algorithm is public.

Only the key must remain secret.

❌ HTTPS hides everything.

Correct:

HTTPS encrypts the data (payload), but metadata such as:

Source IP
Destination IP
Port Numbers

are still visible.

Best Practices
Use strong encryption algorithms.
Protect encryption keys.
Never hardcode keys into applications.
Always use HTTPS instead of HTTP.
Keep cryptographic software updated.
